			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote28-94911_000_033">28.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.15?lang=eng#14" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 128:15</a>; see also <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.18?lang=eng#17" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 128:18</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote29-94911_000_033">29.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/1.30?lang=eng#29" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 1:30</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/21.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 21:2</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/124.118?lang=eng#117" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 124:118</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote30-94911_000_033">30.</a>
      </span>
				<p>In <span class="emphasis">Messages of the First Presidency,</span> comp. James R. Clark, 6 vols. (Salt Lake City: Bookcraft, 1965&ndash;75), 3:256&ndash;57; see also <span class="emphasis">Deseret Semi-Weekly News,</span> 17 Apr. 1894, p. 1.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote31-94911_000_033">31.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Archibald F. Bennett, &ldquo;The Genealogical Society of Utah,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Improvement Era,</span> Apr. 1935, p. 225.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote32-94911_000_033">32.</a>
      </span>
				<p>President Ezra Taft Benson and his counselors issued this statement: &ldquo;In considering ordinances for the deceased, we need not attempt to determine individual worthiness, whether an ordinance will be accepted, or the probable feelings of other deceased individuals affected by the proposed ordinance. &hellip; These determinations must, of necessity, be made beyond the veil&rdquo; (First Presidency Letter, 8 Dec. 1988).</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-94911_000_033">33.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/19.13?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 19:13</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/ether/3.14?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Ether 3:14</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moses 5:9</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-94911_000_033">34.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.58?lang=eng#57" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 138:58</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-94911_000_033">35.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Ibid., <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.58?lang=eng#57" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 138:58</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote36-94911_000_033">36.</a>
      </span>
				<p>President Joseph Fielding Smith wrote: <span class="emphasis">&ldquo;We are not going to do the temple work for everybody because it does not pertain to them. We are going to do the temple work for those who are entitled, through their faith and their repentance, to enter into the celestial kingdom.</span> &hellip; I do not know whether one man is worthy and another is not. The Lord has given us the privilege of doing the work for all of <span class="emphasis">our kindred&rdquo;</span> (<span class="emphasis">Doctrines of Salvation,</span> comp. Bruce R. McConkie, 3 vols., Salt Lake City: Bookcraft, 1954&ndash;55, 2:191; emphasis in original).</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote37-94911_000_033">37.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">Records Submission Manual,</span> 4th ed. (Salt Lake City: Genealogical Society of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, 1973), p. 16.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote38-94911_000_033">38.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">Ensign,</span> July 1994, p. 5.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote39-94911_000_033">39.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See Joseph Fielding Smith, <span class="emphasis">Doctrines of Salvation,</span> comp. Bruce R. McConkie, 3 vols. (Salt Lake City: Bookcraft, 1954&ndash;55), 2:76; Bruce R. McConkie, <span class="emphasis">The Mortal Messiah,</span> 4 vols. (Salt Lake City: Deseret Book Co., 1979&ndash;81), 3:188.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote40-94911_000_033">40.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.41?lang=eng#40" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 9:41</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/41.3?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 41:3</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/137.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 137:9</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-94911_000_033"><a name="-94911_000_033">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote41-94911_000_033">41.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/128.24?lang=eng#23" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 128:24</a>.</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
                                        
